  <entry>
    <title>Programming Languages, UW, Part C - Ruby Basic</title>
    <link href="https://www.thisisxxz.com/2023/07/22/prog-lan-4/"/>
    <id>https://www.thisisxxz.com/2023/07/22/prog-lan-4/</id>
    <published>2023-07-22T08:07:27.000Z</published>
    <updated>2023-07-30T02:27:01.982Z</updated>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;作为一门研究 programming languages 的课程，OOP
是一个避不开的话题。这一节通过介绍 Ruby —— a &lt;em&gt;dynamically typed
OOP&lt;/em&gt; language，来引出 functional v.s. OOP 这一历史悠久的命题。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Taken together, ML, Racket, and Ruby cover three of the four
combinations of functional v.s. object-oriented and statically v.s.
dynamically typed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
